#ministeriumclub

【THU-12-MAR] ↓ info ↓
/// WONDERKIDZ SHOWCASE - Wonderkidz is a Paris-based collective and record label born from a deep connection to underground club culture. For the past two years, they have been hosting events across Europe, from crowded basements in Paris to late-night parties in Italy and Spain. All of their sets are built around energy, friendship, and sharp dance floor instincts. Having recently expanded to Madrid with a residency in Malasaña, Wonderkidz continues to grow its community around resident DJs: Taxi Drivers and Lobo. They deliver honest selections, raw club emotion, and a sense of togetherness that defines their sound.

/// JAMAIMOI - Jamaimoi is a French–Spanish DJ and producer rooted in Lisbon’s underground circuit. His sets trace a loose, percussive line through disco, house, breakbeat, and quirky leftfield club grooves, always laced with a touch of funk and soul. Moving easily between sweaty basements and open-air stages, he channels the pulse of Lisbon and Spain’s restless dancefloor energy.

━☆ ＲŪＭＵ ☆━
ᴇᴀᴛ, ᴅʀɪɴᴋ ɴ’ ᴅᴀɴᴄᴇ - ʀᴜᴀ ɴᴏᴠᴀ ᴅᴀ ᴛʀɪɴᴅᴀᴅᴇ 5ɢ ʟɪꜱʙᴏɴ - ᴠɪꜱɪᴛ ᴏᴜʀ ᴡᴇʙꜱɪᴛᴇ - ɴᴏ ᴘʜᴏɴᴇꜱ ᴏɴ ᴛʜᴇ ᴅᴀɴᴄᴇꜰʟᴏᴏʀ - ʀᴇꜱᴘᴇᴄᴛ ᴛʜᴇ ꜱᴘᴀᴄᴇ ᴀɴᴅ ᴇᴀᴄʜ ᴏᴛʜᴇʀ.

【FRI-13-MAR] ↓ info ↓
/// DORIAN PAIC - Few figures capture Frankfurt’s house and techno heritage like Dorian Paic. From the jet-set disco Dorian Gray and Sven Väth’s Omen to cult spaces like XS, Monza, and Robert Johnson, he’s been a constant presence shaping the city’s rhythm. A longtime force behind Freebase Records and head of the influential label raum…musik, Paic’s deep, hypnotic sound has carried him from intimate floors to Love Family Park, Cocoon nights, and beyond. Always rooted in groove and precision, he remains a cornerstone of the German underground, a DJ’s DJ who plays for those who truly listen.

/// ANDI CAZ - Cornerstone of Porto’s underground scene, known for his deep connection to the dancefloor and his sharp sense of groove. A long-time resident at the legendary Lottus after-hours, he’s perfected the craft of late-night storytelling through sound. Beyond the booth, he runs HomeMade Records and curates nights under the Hypnosis banner, blending his role as DJ, label head, and promoter. With over a decade of releases supported by key players across the scene, Andy Caz continues to shape Porto’s sonic landscape, always authentic, always forward-thinking.

/// DA NI - Selector shaped by the dance floor, blending deep house grooves with raw, unconventional shades of techno. A founding force behind Propaganda 085 alongside Nuno di Rosso and Wailers, he’s carved a path through Portugal’s underground scene with a rebellious spirit. Known for his deep vinyl digging, Da Ni curates rare 90s gems and forgotten tracks that capture the pulse of the era. Behind the decks, his sets unfold like stories — crafted from texture, tension, and timeless rhythm.

━☆ ＲŪＭＵ ☆━
ᴇᴀᴛ, ᴅʀɪɴᴋ ɴ’ ᴅᴀɴᴄᴇ - ʀᴜᴀ ɴᴏᴠᴀ ᴅᴀ  ᴛʀɪɴᴅᴀᴅᴇ 5ɢ ʟɪꜱʙᴏɴ - ᴠɪꜱɪᴛ ᴏᴜʀ ᴡᴇʙꜱɪᴛᴇ - ɴᴏ ᴘʜᴏɴᴇꜱ ᴏɴ ᴛʜᴇ ᴅᴀɴᴄᴇꜰʟᴏᴏʀ - ʀᴇꜱᴘᴇᴄᴛ ᴛʜᴇ ꜱᴘᴀᴄᴇ ᴀɴᴅ ᴇᴀᴄʜ ᴏᴛʜᴇʀ.

【SAT-07-MAR] ↓ info ↓
/// DAVID TRIANA - Born in Bogotá, David Triana channels the warmth and rhythm of his roots into deep, percussive club cuts that move with soul and intention. Co-founder of Downpitch Recordings with Tomás Station, he helped shape Bogotá’s underground through vinyl releases and forward-thinking events connecting local talent with global sounds. Now based in London, Triana co-runs Soursopp, a night known for its vibrant energy at Fabric, Lion & Lamb, and Little Portland Street. With releases on Descendant of The Deep and Moody Records, and appearances on NTS and Red Light Radio, his sound drifts effortlessly between house, jazz, and organic electronics, timeless, groove-driven, and crafted for late-night dancers.

/// MIKOLAÏ - Rooted in Europe’s underground for over two decades, Mikolaï channels a refined blend of minimal tension and deep, hypnotic groove. Based in Lisbon, his residency and programming at Rūmu mirror his patient, immersive approach to sound. Through Picture Perfect Recordings, he extends this spirit further—crafting resonant spaces where rhythm, detail, and emotion converge in timeless motion.

━☆ ＲŪＭＵ ☆━
